SIMPLE: striction
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Striction
<hw>Stric"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>strictio</ets>. See <er>Stringent</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of
constricting, or the state of being constricted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Line of striction</b></col> <fld>(Geom.)</fld>, <cd>the
line on a skew surface that cuts each generator in that point of it that
is nearest to the succeeding generator.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Strictly</ent>⟦br⟧
